“Welcome to the Western Cape, where majestic mountains meet wild, open seas. This is a place of rolling green valleys and vast, untouched plains. A place where you can connect with a diverse group of people. A place where you can find yourself again.” Whether you’re an intrepid explorer or part of an active family, you’ll find no shortage of outdoor activities in the Western Cape, including white-sand beaches, mountains, nature reserves, wildlife, hiking trails, skydiving, zipline adventures, water activities and magnificent sightseeing. Be entertained by the many events during the month of April including the Two Oceans Marathon, World Travel Market Africa, SA Cheese Festival, Rare Plant Fair and many more. Travel from Cape Town and its urban vibe to the 5 diverse regions of the Western Cape: Cape Overberg, Cape Winelands, Garden Route & Klein Karoo, Cape West Coast and Cape Karoo, where you will discover a world of unique experiences. Draw inspiration from the arts and culture, heritage, food and wine and natural beauty of each region.